4) Build Plotly renderer for 3D surfaces and 2D self-check charts — Done
   - Created PlotlyRenderer with 3D surface plotting, z-axis locking, theme support.
   - Added 2D line chart rendering for self-check (term structure and smile slices).

5) Implement UI controls, theme switch, z-axis lock, and debounce LOD — Done
   - Built UIController with slider/select binding, debounced callbacks for LOD.
   - Integrated theme switching and parameter synchronization.

6) Wire tabs (Level-1 and Level-2 Greeks) and integrate all modules — Done
   - Completed App.js with full module integration, tab switching, and rendering pipeline.
   - Added export PNG, copy JSON, and reset view functionality.

7) Verify numeric stability on edges (T→0, deep ITM/OTM) and tune clamps — Done
   - Applied T_min=0.02, sigma_min=0.05, d1/d2 clamping to ±8 range for numerical stability.
   - Used analytical Greeks formulas to avoid finite difference noise.

8) Prepare for Pages deploy (static assets only) — Done
   - Project structure ready for static hosting (index.html + src/ assets).
   - Created README.md with deployment instructions and local testing guide.

